<p>Now letâ€™s try some inline formulas, such as you may except <span>(b \ne 0)</span> in expression <span>(a \over b)</span> and the famous formula <span>(E = mc^2)</span> from Einstein.</p>

<p>However, there are some issues to use MathJex with Markdown because symbols in formula will be parsed by Markdown first. The easiest way to avoid this is surrounding your formula with <code>&lt;span&gt;</code> since Markdown will parse nothing in a html/xml block. Such as <code>&lt;span&gt;\(a \ne 0\)&lt;/span&gt;</code> for a inline formula <span>(a \ne 0)</span>.</p>
